<span id="freeTextContainer12599607058459808478">This was the book that spawned adult reading for me. My mom read it aloud on a car trip to the Smokey Mountains. The characters are engaging and could walk off the page. Truly the first experience I had with characters that i would recognize if they walked into the room.<br/><br/>Fifteen years later, this book remains the only book I&apos;ve ever read that still holds all it&apos;s charm and wonder with each reread. I make a piont to reread it at least every two years. <br/><br/>Cutter Gap and it&apos;s people are very much alive</span>
  <span id="freeText12599607058459808478" style="display:none">This was the book that spawned adult reading for me. My mom read it aloud on a car trip to the Smokey Mountains. The characters are engaging and could walk off the page. Truly the first experience I had with characters that i would recognize if they walked into the room.<br /><br />Fifteen years later, this book remains the only book I've ever read that still holds all it's charm and wonder with each reread. I make a piont to reread it at least every two years. <br /><br />Cutter Gap and it's people are very much alive in Catherine Marshall's writing. A beautiful story of romance, adventure, and coming of age in a time when being true to yourself was the least of your worries.</span>
