    <a title="Mike (the Paladin)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2187043-mike-the-paladin"><img alt="Mike (the Paladin)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528431476p2/2187043.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/77382738?book_show_action=true">Nov 10, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mike (the Paladin)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mike (the Paladin)" href="/user/show/2187043-mike-the-paladin">Mike (the Paladin)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780380440320" href="/book/show/754792.Christy">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer77382738" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17790267275596993206">Not a bad read, more of a romance than I care for. My first girl friend wanted me to read it....nuff said.<br/><br/>Like I said pretty good, follows the story of a young girl as she sets out to help the poor in Appalachia. As someone who grew up in the foothills of the Smokies I&apos;m somewhat ambivalent about that part of the book. Yes it&apos;s a part of the country that has a troubled and difficult past, but there is a certain selfrightousness that goes with a lot of the &quot;do-gooder&quot; attitude I&apos;ve seen.<br/><br/>But, with</span>
  <span id="freeText17790267275596993206" style="display:none">Not a bad read, more of a romance than I care for. My first girl friend wanted me to read it....nuff said.<br /><br />Like I said pretty good, follows the story of a young girl as she sets out to help the poor in Appalachia. As someone who grew up in the foothills of the Smokies I'm somewhat ambivalent about that part of the book. Yes it's a part of the country that has a troubled and difficult past, but there is a certain selfrightousness that goes with a lot of the "do-gooder" attitude I've seen.<br /><br />But, without reveling any more of my own hang-ups, the book is largely a romance with religous overtones. Not for me but not bad.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17790267275596993206" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

